P2 - Recursive Descent Parser
CS 4880 Compiler Design

DESCRIPTION
    Reads source code from a file or stdin, parses it according to the
    course grammar, and prints the parse tree in preorder traversal.

    Lex-only mode (-l flag) emits one line per token instead of the tree.

BUILD
    make
    make clean

    Manual (gcc required):
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c lexer.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c tree.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c parser.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -c P2.c
        gcc -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -std=c11 -g -o P2 P2.o parser.o tree.o lexer.o

RUN
    ./P2 basename        reads basename.ext, prints parse tree
    ./P2 < file.ext      reads from stdin
    ./P2                 reads from stdin (type input, Ctrl+D to end)

    ./P2 -l basename     lex-only mode: prints tokens instead of parse tree
    ./P2 -l < file.ext

PARSE TREE FORMAT
    Nodes are printed in preorder, indented two spaces per level.
    Each line shows the nonterminal label followed by any semantic tokens:

        ID:<name>:<line>     identifier
        #:<value>:<line>     integer
        Op:<sym>:<line>      operator or relational symbol

    Syntactic tokens (keywords, brackets, colons, parentheses) are discarded.

GRAMMAR
    <program>    -> go <vars> <block> exit
    <vars>       -> empty | int identifier = integer <varList> :
    <varList>    -> identifier = integer <varList> | empty
    <block>      -> { <vars> <stats> }
    <stats>      -> <stat> <mStat>
    <mStat>      -> empty | <stat> <mStat>
    <stat>       -> <read> | <print> | <block> | <cond> | <loop> | <assign>
    <read>       -> scan identifier :
    <print>      -> output <exp> :
    <cond>       -> cond [ identifier <relational> <exp> ] <stat>
    <loop>       -> loop [ identifier <relational> <exp> ] <stat>
    <assign>     -> set identifier = <exp> :
    <relational> -> ?le | ?ge | ?lt | ?gt | ?ne | ?eq | = = | ;
    <exp>        -> <M> ** <exp> | <M> // <exp> | <M>
    <M>          -> <N> + <M> | <N>
    <N>          -> <R> - <N> | - <N> | <R>
    <R>          -> ( <exp> ) | identifier | integer

TOKEN TYPES (lexer)
    IDTk      identifier: starts with 'x', followed by letters/digits/underscores, max 8 chars
    IntTk     integer: decimal digits only, max 8 digits
    KW_tk     keyword: go og loop int exit scan output cond then set func program
    OpTk      multi-char operator: ?le ?ge ?lt ?gt ?ne ?eq ** //
    OpDelTk   single-char operator or delimiter: + - : ; = ( ) { } [ ]
    EOFTk     end of input

    Comments (@text@) are consumed silently and do not produce a token.
    Lexical errors print "LEXICAL ERROR: <detail> line <n>" to stderr and exit.
    Syntax errors print "SYNTAX ERROR: expected <X>, got '<Y>' (line <n>)" and exit.

EXAMPLE
    Input:
        go
        int x = 1 :
        { scan x :
          output x + 2 :
        }
        exit

    Output:
        program
          vars ID:x:2 #:1:2
            varList
          block
            stats
              stat
                read ID:x:3
              mStat
                stat
                  print
                    exp
                      M Op:+:4
                        N
                          R ID:x:4
                        M
                          N
                            R #:2:4
                mStat
